How to Fix A Country in 12 Days
I can=E2=80=99t really start writing an essay until I=E2=80=99m under inten=
se time pressure.
Every week, without fail, I try to come up with an idea on Monday, stare at=
 my screen, pace back and forth, go for a run, scroll Twitter, listen to po=
dcasts and read articles for *~inspiration~*, stare at my screen some more,=
 open up a Google Doc and put [Title to Come] at the top, set the font to S=
pectral, font size to 18, bold it, then go back to Spectral 11 regular to w=
rite [Title Image to Come] on the next line, hit enter a couple times, star=
t writing a few sentences to see if anything sticks, delete them, get up, p=
ace, run, and repeat.=C2=A0
Then, magically, as normal peoples=E2=80=99 clocks wind down to Beer O=E2=
=80=99Clock on Friday afternoon, inspiration strikes. For the next ~60 hour=
s, the hours that normal people spend hanging out with friends and family a=
nd relaxing and stuff, I write like a man possessed. Words flow from my fin=
gers like wine and flock to my screen like the Salmon of Capistrano. By Mon=
day morning (or Tuesday, this summer), I=E2=80=99ve somehow written like 8,=
000 words, I make that [Title Image], hit send, and start the whole process=
 again.=C2=A0Time pressure is good.=20
So I wasn=E2=80=99t surprised at all to see my home state, Pennsylvania, ab=
solutely thrive under self-imposed time pressure. They fixed I-95, served u=
p Dalessandro=E2=80=99s [ https://substack.com/redirect/5f9f3f81-4807-4bfa-=
bb6d-a06ddb513cd2?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU ]-steak-sized heaps of civic pride, and laid down a template to f=
ix pretty much everything that ails the country, all in 12 days.
It=E2=80=99s no secret that America can=E2=80=99t build things as fast as w=
e used to. Americans built the Empire State Building in just 410 days; NYC=
=E2=80=99s Second Avenue Subway project, California=E2=80=99s High-Speed Ra=
